<h3>IncRange( [address] , [start] , [end] );</h3>
<ul>
    <li>[address] - the address to increment</li>
    <li>[start] - starting value</li>
    <li>[end] - if increase would hit this value, roll over to [start]</li>
</ul>


<h3>Description</h3>
<p>Increases the value at the address with 1. If increasing the value would cause value to hit [end], stores [start] to value instead.
</p>

<p>Notice that if variable value is outside the [start]Â and [end] range when calling this, function might misbehave.</p>

<h3>Examples</h3>

<code>
incRange(my_variable, 0, 100);  // increase my_variable by 1, keeping it between 0 and 99
incRange(my_array[i], 10, 13);  // increase my_array[i] by 1, keeping it between 10 and 12
</code>
